<subSubSection id="CFA3F4A19655131C718DE55EFCDCFDCF" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8706A72A9655131C718DE55EFCDCFDCF" blockId="9.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis id="B5CD7B389655131C718DE55EFEDFFE97" bold="true" box="[199,308,297,323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="40B9DCA99655131C7009E55EFDCCFE97" authority="Vlasak &amp; Santos-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vlasak &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[323,551,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danielvlasaki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B5CD7B389655131C7009E55EFDCCFE97" box="[323,551,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Apeba danielvlasaki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AEFEC6439655131C7364E55EFD6DFE97" box="[558,646,297,323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="40B9DCA99655131C7253E55EFB51FE90" authority="(Galileo &amp; Martins, 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[793,1210,297,324]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="popeba">
<emphasis id="B5CD7B389655131C7253E55EFC60FE97" box="[793,907,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">A. popeba</emphasis>
(Galileo &amp; Martins, 2006)
</taxonomicName>
(see photographs at 
<bibRefCitation id="E328DADB9655131C71DDE53AFEDDFEB3" author="Bezark, L. G." box="[151,310,333,359]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" refId="ref10888" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2019 a) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the World. New World Cerambycidae Catalog. Available from: http: // bezbycids. com / byciddb / wdefault. asp? w = n (accessed 23 November 2019)" type="url" year="2019">Bezark 2019a</bibRefCitation>
), a species described and known from 
<collectingCountry id="FFAEE7BA9655131C73ADE53AFC8FFEB3" box="[743,868,333,359]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, but differs as follows: posterior third of pronotum with two black, large semicircular maculae, one on each side; dense yellow pronotal pubescence obscuring integument on light area; and lower eye lobes distinctly shorter than gena (
<figureCitation id="1F82BBAF9655131C72D8E5E2FC0EFE7B" box="[914,997,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22. 17–21" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,590,1637]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1411,561,1654]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. 17–21) Apeba danielvlasaki, holotype female: 17) Dorsal habitus; 18) Ventral habitus; 19) Lateral habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Head, lateral view. 22) Apeba popeba, head, lateral view, female from Costa Rica (photograph by Larry G. Bezark)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701069/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). In female of 
<taxonomicName id="40B9DCA99655131C75C2E5E2FB13FE7B" baseAuthorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[1160,1272,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="popeba">
<emphasis id="B5CD7B389655131C75C2E5E2FB13FE7B" box="[1160,1272,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">A. popeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the pronotum is entirely orangish, pronotal pubescence does not obscure integument, and the lower eye lobes are about as long as gena (
<figureCitation id="1F82BBAF9655131C71B0E5AAFEA4FE23" box="[250,335,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22. 17–21" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1679,1704]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,590,1637]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1411,561,1654]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. 17–21) Apeba danielvlasaki, holotype female: 17) Dorsal habitus; 18) Ventral habitus; 19) Lateral habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Head, lateral view. 22) Apeba popeba, head, lateral view, female from Costa Rica (photograph by Larry G. Bezark)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701069/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Although elytral color pattern is variable in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="40B9DCA99655131C7542E5AAFBBBFE23" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1991" box="[1032,1104,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5CD7B389655131C7542E5AAFBBBFE23" box="[1032,1104,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and other related genera, we have never seen variation of pronotal color and pubescence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
